Inputs\: _PROCESS_INSTANCE_ID - Process Instance Id _processInstanceState - Process Instance State (Use value from selection list CSA-ProcessInstance-State) Result\: _processInstanceState -Updated Process Instance State 12ecc5c5-cd12-472c-acd2-f3112962fdaa.46e41e47-ae2f-4eb6-bcb4-84941effdbc6.prompt=Process Instance ID 12ecc5c5-cd12-472c-acd2-f3112962fdaa.54cade4a-433d-4a39-91e0-dd3f612e65cd.description=
This operation iterates through a list of values. It is not recommended to modify the value of the "list" and "separator" inputs during the iteration process.

Inputs\:
    list - The list to iterate through.
    separator - A delimiter separating the list elements.
Default value\: ‘,’ (comma) 

Results\:
    resultString - The current list element (if the response is "has more").

Responses\:
    has more - Another value was found in the list and it has been returned.
    no more - The iterator has gone through the entire list. This response is returned once per list iteration.  A subsequent call to the List iterator operation restarts the list iteration process.
    failure - The operation completed unsuccessfully.

Note\:
   The position of the iterator in the list is tracked by each step's unique identifier. Therefore, you can simultaneously iterate through the same list from multiple steps.

12ecc5c5-cd12-472c-acd2-f3112962fdaa.8fc1dc9b-c7ee-4a25-b522-59cb39faafea.prompt=Process Instance ID 12ecc5c5-cd12-472c-acd2-f3112962fdaa.9873b026-2968-4635-a0fd-9d1209e9d8f2.prompt=Artifact ID 12ecc5c5-cd12-472c-acd2-f3112962fdaa.987f99b4-9b89-4569-9b0c-0c887adf58b3.description=Criado o fluxo para que faça a chamada ao fluxo remoção do host do DNS utilizando a API do DNS e utilizando as operações de HTTP Client do OO, conforme a quantidade de retentativas definida no caso de apresentar falha na exclusão. Este fluxo tem os seguintes parâmetros de entrada\: retries - quantidade de vezes que o fluxo de exclusão de host do DNS será executado host - hostname completo (FQDN) do host a ser excluido do DNS zona - Zona DNS que o host a ser excluido faz parte. Se não for informado tal parametro, o fluxo utilizará o valor de host (esperando que tenha o FQDN) Com base nesses parametros serão feitas chamadas para exclusão do host no DNS pelo número de vezes definido, caso o mesmo resulte em falha na execução. 12ecc5c5-cd12-472c-acd2-f3112962fdaa.98a85b52-04d0-4657-8868-17a74edf8d4f.description=This workflow updates the Process Instance State using PEM API. Inputs\: _PROCESS_INSTANCE_ID - Process Instance Id _processInstanceState - Process Instance State (Use value from selection list CSA-ProcessInstance-State) Result\: _processInstanceState -Updated Process Instance State 12ecc5c5-cd12-472c-acd2-f3112962fdaa.9cf3f954-a165-4f7c-b5eb-3a49623a79dc.prompt=User Identifier 12ecc5c5-cd12-472c-acd2-f3112962fdaa.a830a07b-ffeb-4870-aaff-7e0295d52b47.description=
This operation runs a command, allowing you to specify whether it runs locally (no port to be specified), via SSH, Global Shell, ROSH, Telnet, or RSH.

Inputs\:
    host - The host name or IP address.
    port - The port number used to connect to the host.
    username - The user name used to connect.
    password - The password associated with the "username" input. If using a private key file, this is the passphrase for the file.
    protocol - The protocol used to run the command. 
Valid values\: SSH, ROSH, GlobalShell, Telnet, RSH, REXEC, local, WMI, NASConnectTelnet, HPOM
    timeout - The time to wait for the command to complete (in milliseconds). Increase this value if you are getting incomplete output results or a timeout.
Default value\: 90000 (90 seconds), 600000 (if protocol->WMI)
    command - The command to run.
    arguments - The arguments to pass to the command.
    environment - Specifies the environment variables and values that need to be defined when running the command.
    startDir - The path to the starting directory.
    pty - Specifies whether to use pty (used by SSH, GlobalShell)
Valid values\: true, false
Default value\: false
    privateKeyFile - The absolute path to the private key file on the RAS host (used by SSH, GlobalShell).
    sasHost - The host on which to run the ROSH command.
    sasHostUsername - The user name used to run the ROSH command on "sasHost".
    usernamePrompt - The prompt message for the user name. Used by the Telnet protocol. 
Default value\: When used by the NASConnectTelnet protocol, the default value is "NAS Login\:".
    passwordPrompt - The prompt message for the password associated with the "usernamePrompt"  input. Used by the Telnet protocol.  
Default value\: When used by the 'NASConnectTelnet' protocol, the default value is "Password\:"
    outputPath - The network accessible path where to store the temporary files. If you do not specify this input, it points to '\\host\admin$\temp\'. If this path is not accessible, change it to use another share to which the host local system account has write access. By default, the path needs to be changed on Windows 2000 systems.
    nasDevice - The NAS device on which to run the command when using the 'NASConnect' protocol.
    nasDeviceConsoleMode - The NAS device console mode used to run the command scripts running the command on the specified NAS device. If you leave this input empty, command scripts are not used, and the connections to the NAS device and the command are issued directly in the console. This is not recommended. Due to error handling capabilities limitation, the result might be a success even if the command failed to run. You can find the values for this input in the NAS web interface, as a drop-down list when creating a new command script (for example, Cisco IOS enable).
    hpomNode - The node on which to run the command.
    hpomProtocol - The protocol used to communicate with HPOM 
Valid values\: HTTP or HTTPS.
    characterSet - The name of the character set used for stream encoding and decoding between the RAS and target machine.
Valid values\: SJIS,EUC-JP, UTF-8
Default value\: UTF-8 (used by SSH, GlobalShell, Telnet, RSH, REXEC)

Hidden Inputs\:
    useDelegation - This input only applies to the WMI protocol. If set to "true" the operation will use the 'Delegate' impersonation level and the 'Kerberos' authentication protocol. If 'false', empty or missing the operation will use 'Impersonate' for the impersonation level and the default authentication protocol (which is NTLM).
Valid values\: true, false
Default value\: false

Results\:
    returnResult - This is the primary output. Used to determine the operation response, specifying whether the operation is successful or not.
    stdOut - The standard output (STDOUT) of the command.
    stdErr - The standard error (STDERR) of the command.
    exitStatus - Every command returns an exit status (sometimes referred to as a return status or exit code). A successful command returns a 0, while an unsuccessful one returns a non-zero value that usually can be interpreted as an error code. The supported protocols are\: SSH, ROSH, GlobalShell, local, WMI. 
Examples\: 0 for a successful command, 126 if the command cannot execute.

Responses\:
    success - The operation completed as stated in the description.
    failure - The operation completed unsuccessfully or if the command was not yet terminated.

Notes\:
1. Telnet protocol - Since telnet is a shell protocol, not a remote execution protocol, the response is always  successful if the command is ran in the remote shell.  The return code of the specified command cannot be determined in this protocol.  If you must use the telnet protocol with this operation, make sure to check the command results. Consider using the SSH or REXEC protocol instead.
2. The "exitStatus" result for Telnet, RSH, REXEC, NasConnectTelnet, HPOM will be "" (empty). For Windows host, it will be run the following final command\: "cmd /V\:on /c   ^& echo \!ERRORLEVEL\!". For Linux host, the "; echo $?" will be appended to "command" input or "arguments" input (if the last one is not empty). 
3. If RSH protocol is used the command should be run from a machine that is in the same network as the one from the host input.
4. WMI protocol can be used only from Windows RAS. If you want to make connection from a non Windows RAS use other protocols like SSH, Telnet.
12ecc5c5-cd12-472c-acd2-f3112962fdaa.ae67d520-7ed3-4de4-b420-40fab03735a1.description=
This operation loops as many times as specified in the "count" input, counting from "1" to a greater number, incrementing it by "1" at each iteration.

Inputs\:
    count - The number of loops to complete.
Valid values\: from 1 to 9223372036854775807
    reset - Specifies whether the counter restarts counting from "1".
Valid values\: true, false
Default value\: false
    to - The number to count to. It will take the value of the "count" input field. 
    from - The number to start counting at. For this operation, it is customized to "1".
    incrementBy - The number to increment by while counting. For this operation, it is customized to "1".

Results\:
    resultString – This is the primary output. It contains the value of the number that was just counted.

Responses\:
    has more – The counting process is not complete. One or more iterations are pending.
    no more – The counting process is complete.
    failure - The operation completed unsuccessfully.

Note\:
1. It is recommended that you do not change the values of the "to", "from" or "incrementBy" input fields.
2. The "from", "to" and "incrementBy" inputs are customized for this operation. Even though you can also customize them, if you need to specify the loop range borders and the increment value, use the "Counter" operation.

Examples\:
1. For a loop with 20 iterations, the following values should be provided for the input fields\:
    count\: 20
    reset\: false (this field can also be left blank, as "false" is the default value)
2. For an infinite loop, the value of "count" should be at least "1" and the value of "reset" should be "true".

12ecc5c5-cd12-472c-acd2-f3112962fdaa.c69ee5e6-f901-46a5-8c4b-0234b06a9d53.prompt=Hostname (FQDN) 12ecc5c5-cd12-472c-acd2-f3112962fdaa.description=
DNS Undeploy. 

Inputs Parameters\:

 CSA_CONTEXT_ID – CSA Context Id
 CSA_PROCESS_ID – CSA Process Instance Id
 SVC_COMPONENT_ID - This token will resolve to the Service component Id. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\:SVC_COMPONENT_ID]
 RSC_PROVIDER_ID - This token will resolve to the Resource Provider Id that was selected at the Subscription time. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\:RSC_PROVIDER_ID]
 SVC_SUBSCRIPTION_EMAIL - This token will resolve to the subscriber’s email address. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: SVC_SUBSCRIPTION_EMAIL]
 RSC_SUBSCRIPTION_ID - This token will resolve to the Resource Subscription Id that was created from the Resource Offering at the Subscription time.
  		Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: RSC_SUBSCRIPTION_ID]
 SVC_COMPONENT_TYPE - This token will resolve to the Service component type. Eg\: Server.. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: SVC_COMPONENT_TYPE]
 RSC_POOL_ID - This token will resolve to the Resource pool Id that was selected at the Subscription time. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: RSC_POOL_ID]
 SVC_INSTANCE_ID - This token will resolve to the Service Instance Id. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: SVC_INSTANCE_ID]
 SVC_SUBSCRIPTION_ID - This token will resolve to the Subscription Id that was created at the Subscription time. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: SVC_SUBSCRIPTION_ID]
 PRN_COMPONENT_ID – This token will resolve to the parent Component’s Service Component Id. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: PRN_COMPONENT_ID]
 REQ_ORG_ID - This token will resolve to the Organization Id associated with the service request. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: REQ_ORG_ID]
 REQ_USER_ID - This token will resolve to the User Id associated with the service request. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: REQ_USER_ID]
 USR_ORG_ID - This token will resolve to the Organization Id associated with the subscriber. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: USR_ORG_ID]
 RSC_BINDING_ID - This token will resolve to the Resource Binding Id that was created at the Subscription time. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: RSC_BINDING_ID]

Responses\:
 success - The operation completed successfully.
 failure - Something went wrong.
12ecc5c5-cd12-472c-acd2-f3112962fdaa.e7866ddf-bcad-49e8-87e3-ad6f69697b4e.description=
Compares two strings, returning a true response if and only if they contain the same sequence of characters. A null string is considered to be equal to an empty string.

Inputs\:
    string1 - The first string. 
Default value\: "" (empty)
    string2 - The second string.
Default value\: "" (empty)
    ignoreCase - If set to 'true', then the comparison ignores case considerations. The two strings are considered equal ignoring case if they are of the same length and corresponding characters in the two strings are equal ignoring case. If set to any value other than 'true', then the strings must match exactly to be considered equal.

Responses\:
    true - If the two strings are equal.
    false - If the two strings are not equal.
